<br>
However, from the Quests section of Graffe I obtained the following information:<br>
<br>
&quot;Heart of Fire - In Solusek A, I was near the Solusek's Champion when a wizard spawned that had this. The hearts are semi rare. Wizards and Shamans share spawning points so by killing shamans you increase your chances of finding a wizard with one of these. They only drop from Inferno Goblin Wizards. If you want to save yourself a headache, go into Solusek A during peak hours and OOC that you would like to loot one in return for some platinum.&quot;<br>
<br>
Is all of this information still valid according to what we know? Is it in fact ONLY Inferno Goblin Wizards that drop the heart? Are Shaman actually the placeholders or is anything a placeholder?<br>
<br>
Looking forward to finishing this quest that I should have done 20 levels ago. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orsmoxlorr>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 615<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/02 9:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated...</span><hr size=1> from what i've seen only wizards drop te heart.  As for placeholders.  I think any type of goblin will spawn at any point.  So just wipe as many as you see, <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66366">Baron Orsmo Xlorr 59.73 Lvl Wizard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
